01:17.318 --> 01:18.685
You nervous?

01:34.702 --> 01:36.536
Jacob?

01:47.815 --> 01:49.880
Jacob, are you hiding?

02:03.363 --> 02:05.029
Jacob?

02:08.668 --> 02:09.735
Hmm.

02:09.737 --> 02:13.372
I wonder where Jacob could be.

02:13.374 --> 02:14.973
Hey!

02:14.975 --> 02:18.142
- I got you.
- Yeah, you got me.

02:18.144 --> 02:21.513
What are you doing up in the attic? You
know you're not supposed to be up here.

02:21.515 --> 02:23.581
I, um, was hiding.

02:23.583 --> 02:25.616
Yeah. Well, why don't
we get your best-man clothes on

02:25.618 --> 02:27.753
- so we can get this show on the road.
- No thank you.

02:27.755 --> 02:30.055
Whoa!

02:30.057 --> 02:32.758
Hey, hey, hey. The sooner
we get this over with,

02:32.760 --> 02:35.063
the sooner we can
all have cake.

02:36.397 --> 02:38.930
I don't wanna wear the tie.

02:38.932 --> 02:40.398
You're gonna look
really good with the tie on.

02:40.400 --> 02:41.699
You're gonna look like me.

02:41.701 --> 02:45.771
Then I want two...

02:45.773 --> 02:47.572
- pieces of cake.
- Deal.

02:47.574 --> 02:53.912
And I want a real train set,
with lights, bridges and houses.

02:53.914 --> 02:55.947
You drive a hard bargain.

02:55.949 --> 02:58.849
Let's go get married.

02:58.851 --> 03:03.054
And now, Mark and Elizabeth
will recite their vows.

03:03.056 --> 03:05.657
No pressure, just pretend
like we're not here.

03:07.761 --> 03:10.865
I, uh...

03:12.632 --> 03:15.499
Uh, summer before law school

03:15.501 --> 03:20.771
I spent half my financial-aid
money on a really expensive bike,

03:20.773 --> 03:24.475
and then I crashed it
in some middle-of-nowhere trail,

03:24.477 --> 03:26.812
but was lucky,

03:26.814 --> 03:30.681
because there was this beautiful
girl out hiking that day.

03:30.683 --> 03:34.618
- Me.
- And she gave me her whole pack of Life Savers.

03:35.988 --> 03:37.858
And kissed me...

03:38.892 --> 03:40.728
to take my mind
off the pain.

03:43.564 --> 03:45.764
Thank you
for saving my life.

03:45.766 --> 03:49.166
I vow to make it up
to you every day.

03:49.168 --> 03:51.703
I was kinda hoping you'd vow
to fix up this house.

03:51.705 --> 03:54.708
Yeah, all right. I'll do that, too.

03:56.243 --> 03:58.679
- And Elizabeth.
- Oh.

04:00.247 --> 04:01.749
Hold that.

04:02.516 --> 04:04.816
We had, um,
eight years,

04:04.818 --> 04:08.118
one child,
one unrealized dream house,

04:08.120 --> 04:10.955
your law school, and my MFA to think
about this whole marriage thing,

04:10.957 --> 04:15.259
and now I don't know
why it took us so long,

04:15.261 --> 04:17.598
because there is no me
without you.

04:19.699 --> 04:21.266
Is that it?
Are we married?

04:21.267 --> 04:22.533
Ring.

04:22.535 --> 04:25.138
- OK.
- All right?

04:27.508 --> 04:28.609
Thank you.

04:35.883 --> 04:37.785
OK.

04:44.223 --> 04:46.624
- And now, by the power vested in me
- It fits.

04:46.626 --> 04:49.961
- by the Church of Universal Life and the Internet,
- Come here.

04:49.963 --> 04:52.596
I finally pronounce you
husband and wife,

04:52.598 --> 04:54.031
and you're already kissing the bride,

04:54.033 --> 04:56.167
So my work here is done.

04:56.169 --> 04:57.836
Time for cake!

04:57.838 --> 04:59.207
Cake!

06:17.884 --> 06:19.216
Time for the honeymoon?

06:19.218 --> 06:22.155
Yeah, it's time
for the honeymoon.

